	<div class="splash splash-one text-left">
		<div class="section floating-header">
			<p>Reaching Martha’s Vineyard</p>
		</div>	
		<div class="section floating-credit">
			<p><em> Larry Glick</em></p>
		</div>	
	</div>
	<div class="section copy-one">
		<h2>Welcome to the Vineyard Gazette Media Group</h2>
		<p class="tagline">
			<strong>Dedicated to the island of Martha’s Vineyard</strong>
		and the people near and far who love it, the Vineyard Gazette Media Group is an independent media company that combines a commitment
		to excellence in journalism with a passion for innovation across platforms.
		</p>
		<p class="tagline">
		Now embarking on our 178th year, we reach more than<strong> 2.3 million people annually in print and online</strong> with an array of award-winning publications that celebrate the Island’s diverse culture.
		</p>
		<p class="tagline">
		Our flagship newspaper, the <strong>Vineyard Gazette</strong>, and the eponymous <strong>Martha’s Vineyard</strong> magazine, set the standards for high-quality photography, design, content and community engagement that characterize all our magazines, websites, newsletters and events.
		</p>
	</div>	



















	<div class="splash splash-two text-left" style="height: 300px;" id="print">
		<div class="section floating-header">
			<p>News. Culture. Community.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="section floating-credit">
			<p><em> Allen Green </em></p>
		</div>	
	</div>


	<div class="section logos-listed">
		<h2>Print</h2>
				<p class="bold"> We take pride in the quality of our many print publications, from the striking black-and-white newspaper we print onsite at our historic headquarters to the glossy full-color magazines that showcase the vibrancy of the Island.		</p>
		<div class="print-list" style="display: flex;">
			<div style="flex: 58%; margin-right: 4%;">
				<p>
				The weekly <a href="https://vineyardgazette.com" target="_blank" class="black">Vineyard Gazette</a>, has been the Island’s trusted community newspaper since 1846, reporting the news, examining the issues, profiling the people and highlighting the events that shape Martha’s Vineyard.
				</p><p>
				<a href="https://mvmagazine.com" target="_blank" class="black">Martha’s Vineyard magazine</a>, the Island’s premier lifestyle magazine, is published seven times a year, including two issues devoted to <a href="https://vineyardgazettestore.com/product/12/view" target="_blank" class="black">Home & Garden</a>. Combining first-rate magazine journalism with superb photography, it is also home to the popular Best of the Vineyard contest.
				</p>
				<p>
				With the largest circulation of any publication on the Island, <a href="https://vineyardgazette.com/vine" target="_blank" class="black">The Vine</a> highlights the individuals, businesses and organizations that make the Vineyard unique.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div style="flex: 48%;">
				<p>
				<a href="https://mvislandweddings.com" target="_blank" class="black">Island Weddings</a> magazine, published twice a year, features ideas and inspiration from real  celebrations.
				</p>
				<p>
				The stunning <a href="https://vineyardgazettestore.com/product/18/view" target="_blank" class="black">Island Guide</a>, updated every year, offers best bets and highlights for visitors to the Vineyard.
				</p><p>
				The <a href="https://vineyardgazettestore.com/product/9/view" target="_blank" class="black">Real Estate Yearbook</a> summarizes the year in real estate on Martha's Vineyard, with detailed data and photos of every transaction.
				</p><p>
				Designed for day-trippers and weekend visitors, <a href="https://mvol.com/" target="_blank" class="black">Welcome to Martha’s Vineyard</a> is a handy pocket-sized guide to the Island
				</p>
			</div>	
		</div>
	</div>










	<div class="splash splash-three text-right" style="height: 300px;" id="digital">
		<div class="section floating-header">
			<p>Food. Arts. Activities.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="section floating-credit">
			<p><em> Elizabeth Cecil</em></p>
		</div>	
	</div>


	<div class="section logos-listed">
		<h2>Digital</h2>
				<p class="bold"> Honored repeatedly by the New England Newspaper Publishers Association for excellence in digital strategy, the Vineyard Gazette Media Group’s portfolio of digital products includes mobile-optimized websites, newsletters and social media sites.</p>
		<div class="digital-list" style="display: flex;">
			<div style="flex: 58%; margin-right: 4%;">
				<p>
				Our largest website, <a href="https://vineyardgazette.com" target="_blank" class="black">vineyardgazette.com</a>, is accessed by more than 2.3 million unique visitors per year and is updated multiple times each day with breaking news, analysis, opinion and photography. In 2020, the site was named best small newspaper website in the national Eppy Awards, sponsored by Editor and Publisher Magazine.
				</p><p>
				For home cooks and people who love to eat, digital-only <a href="https://mvmagazine.com/cook-the-vineyard" target="_blank" class="black">cookthevineyard.com</a> features menu inspiration, cooking tips and scores of delicious recipes organized by ingredients — many grown on Martha’s Vineyard.
				</p>
				<p>
				Welcome to Martha's Vineyard at <a href="https://mvol.com/" target="_blank" class="black">welcometomarthasvineyard.com</a> is the Island’s original and most comprehensive online directory of visitor information. Founded in 1995, it was acquired by the Vineyard Gazette in 2017.
				</p>
				<p>
				The Complete <a href="https://calendar.vineyardgazette.com/" target="_blank" class="black">Martha’s Vineyard Calendar</a> is the go-to source for all activities and events on Martha’s Vineyard, relied on by the Island Chamber of Commerce, among others.

				</p>
			</div>
			<div style="flex: 48%;">
				<p>
				The website of Martha’s Vineyard magazine, <a href="https://mvmagazine.com/" target="_blank" class="black">mvmagazine.com</a>, features current and archival content from the print magazine, including the results of the annual Best of the Vineyard readers' choice contest. Island Weddings magazine is also online at <a href="https://mvislandweddings.com/" target="_blank" class="black">mvislandweddings.com</a>.
				</p>
				<p>
				Our three email newsletters reach a combined audience of more than 20,000 people, five days a week. <a href="https://vineyardgazette.com/advertise-on-marthas-vineyard/vineyard-gazette-newsletters" target="_blank" class="black">The Broadsheet</a>, published Tuesdays and Fridays, offers the latest news headlines. <a href="https://vineyardgazette.com/advertise-on-marthas-vineyard/vineyard-gazette-newsletters" target="_blank" class="black">Cook the Vineyard</a>, delivered Wednesday mornings, offers timely recipes and food news. <a href="https://vineyardgazette.com/advertise-on-marthas-vineyard/vineyard-gazette-newsletters" target="_blank" class="black">Island Time</a> reaches mailboxes Thursday mornings with best bets for Island-based events for the coming week. 
				</p><p>
				You can also find our brands on Instagram, Facebook and Twitter.
				</p>
			</div>	
		</div>
	</div>
















	<div class="splash splash-four text-left">
		<div class="section floating-header" id="events">
			<p>Lifestyle. Weddings. Real Estate.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="section floating-credit">
			<p><em> Ashley Tilton </em></p>
