	<div class="section copy-two">
		<h2>Our Events</h2>
		<p class="bold"> The Vineyard Gazette Media Group hosts and sponsors a variety of high-profile events each year on Martha’s Vineyard that cater to year-round Islanders, seasonal residents and visitors. 
		</p>
		<div class="event-list" style="display: flex;">
			<div style="flex: 58%; margin-right: 4%;">
				<p>
				Martha’s Vineyard Magazine’s <strong class="black">Best of the Vineyard Party</strong> signals the launch of the summer season with a celebration announcing the magazine’s signature readers’ choice awards in dozens of categories, from best burger to best romantic getaway. Held annually in June, the event features food, music and merriment. 
				</p><p>
				The summer <strong class="black">Car-B-Q Classic</strong> combines a classic car parade and show with an outdoor barbeque picnic on the scenic lawn of the Winnetu Oceanside Resort.
				</p>
<p><strong class="black">Martha’s Party Wedding & Event Conference</strong> in May brings together wedding planners, vendors and others involved in the flourishing event business on Martha’s Vineyard for three days of networking, panel discussions and fun.
 </p>
			<p>
				<strong class="black">Cook the Vineyard </strong>features cookbook authors and food writers in a variety of settings.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div style="flex: 48%;">
	
				<p>
				<strong class="black">Tuesdays in the Newsroom</strong> invites readers to meet and question an eclectic mix of speakers in the intimate setting of the Vineyard Gazette newsroom.
				</p>
<p>
<strong class="black">Juneteenth Jubilee on Martha’s Vineyard</strong> celebrates America’s newest national holiday with family oriented activities
and educational events that focus on enslaved people who escaped to freedom by sea.  </p>

				<p>
				<strong class="black">The Martha’s Vineyard Book Festival</strong> brings world-class authors to the Island for lectures, interviews and panels discussions. 
				</p><p>
				</p>
			</div>	
		</div>
	</div>	











