		<div class="section floating-header" id="about"><p>Enlightening. Engaging. Entertaining.</p></div>
		<div class="section floating-credit">
			<p><em> Larry Glick </em></p>
		</div>	
	</div>

	<div class="section copy-three">
		<h2>About Us</h2>
		<p class="bold">
		It all began in 1846, in the heyday of the whaling era, when Edgar Marchant founded the Vineyard Gazette, pledging to create a newspaper that was “Neutral in Politics . . . devoted to General News, Literature, Morality, Agriculture and Amusement.” 
		</p>
		<p class="bold">
		178 years later, the Vineyard Gazette remains the Island’s trusted source of Island news, still printed every week at the back of our historic home in the village of Edgartown. Today, the Vineyard Gazette Media Group is a multi-media publishing company with an award-winning portfolio that includes magazines, websites, newsletters and events. 
		</p>
		<p class="bold">
		Independent, community-minded and committed to the highest standards of journalism and design, the Vineyard Gazette Media Group is singularly dedicated to the island of Martha’s Vineyard.
		</p>	
	</div>











	<div class="splash splash-six text-right">
		<div class="section floating-header"><p> Unparalleled reach.<br /> Exceptional demographics.</p></div>
		<div class="section floating-credit">
			<p><em> Jeanna Shepard </em></p>
		</div>	
	</div>

	<div class="section copy-four" id="advertise">
		<h2>Advertise</h2>
		<p class="tagline bold">The Vineyard Gazette Media Group is the largest news and information company dedicated to the island of Martha’s Vineyard and the people near and far who love it. Let us help connect you to the customers you want.</p>

		<p class="bold">Through our network of print and digital products and high-profile events, we regularly reach more than 2.3 million consumers: year-round and seasonal residents, visitors and people with an affinity for Martha's Vineyard.</p>

		<p class="bold">In addition to our wide reach, our audience is educated, affluent and engaged.</p>
		<div style="display: flex;" class="bold">
			<div style="flex: 50%;">
				<ul>
					<li>90 percent are college-educated.</li>
					<li>83 percent have spent 15 or more years on Martha’s Vineyard.</li>
					<li>79 percent are homeowners.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div style="flex: 50%;">
				<ul>
					<li>37 percent own three or more cars.</li>
					<li>66 percent earn more than  $100,000 annually and 28 percent earn over $250,000 a year. </li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
		<p style="text-align: right;"><small><em>Source: Harris Interactive Survey, 2013.</em></small></p>
